288  /**
289   * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement}, mostly, if not exclusively, for use by {@link
290   * SyntheticAnnotationMirror} instances.
291   *
292   * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
293   * must not be {@code null}
294   *
295   * @param fullyQualifiedName the fully qualified name of the synthetic element; must conform to Java classname
296   * restrictions; must not be {@code null}
297   *
298   * @param elements a {@link List} of {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}s modeling the annotation elements; must not be
299   * {@code null}
300   *
301   * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
302   *
303   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if {@code fullyQualifiedName} does not conform to Java classname restrictions
304   *
305   * @see SyntheticAnnotationElement
306   *
307   * @see SyntheticAnnotationMirror
308   */
309  public SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
310                                        final SyntheticName fullyQualifiedName,
311                                        final List<? extends SyntheticAnnotationElement> elements) {
312    super();
313    this.annotationMirrors = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>(annotationMirrors);
314    final String fqn = fullyQualifiedName.toString();
315    final int i = fqn.lastIndexOf('.');
316    this.sn = i >= 0 ? new SyntheticName(fqn.substring(i + 1)) : fullyQualifiedName;
317    this.fqn = fullyQualifiedName;
318    this.type = new Type();
319    if (elements.isEmpty()) {
320      this.elements = List.of();
321    } else {
322      final List<InternalAnnotationElement> elements0 = new ArrayList<>(elements.size());
323      for (final SyntheticAnnotationElement e : elements) {
324        elements0.add(new InternalAnnotationElement(e.annotationMirrors(), e.type(), e.name(), e.defaultValue()));
325      }
326      this.elements = unmodifiableList(elements0);
327    }
328  }

423  // See https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1
424  private static final TypeMirror validateScalarType(final TypeMirror type) {
425    if (validAnnotationInterfaceElementScalarType(type)) {
426      return type;
427    }
428    throw new IllegalArgumentException("type: " + type);
429  }

437  /**
438   * An <strong>experimental</strong> collection of information out of which a synthetic annotation element may be
439   * fashioned.
440   *
441   * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson" target="_top">Laird Nelson</a>
442   *
443   * @see SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement#SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement(List, SyntheticName, List)
444   */
445  public static final class SyntheticAnnotationElement {
446
447
448    /*
449     * Instance fields.
450     */
451
452
453    private final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors;
454
455    private final TypeMirror type;
456
457    private final SyntheticName name;
458
459    private final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue;

461

463     * Constructors.
464     */
465
466
467    /**
468     * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}.
469     *
470     * @param type the type of the annotation element; must conform to Java annotation element type restrictions; must
471     * not be {@code null}
472     *
473     * @param name the name of the annotation element; must conform to Java method naming requirements; must not be
474     * {@code null}
475     *
476     * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
477     *
478     * @exception IllegalArgumentException if any argument does not conform to its requirements
479     *
480     * @see #SyntheticAnnotationElement(List, TypeMirror, SyntheticName, SyntheticAnnotationValue)
481     *
482     * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1 Java Language Specification,
483     * section 9.6.1
484     */
485    public SyntheticAnnotationElement(final TypeMirror type, // the "return type"
486                                      final SyntheticName name) {
487      this(List.of(), type, name, null);
488    }
489
490    /**
491     * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}.
492     *
493     * @param type the type of the annotation element; must conform to Java annotation element type restrictions; must
494     * not be {@code null}
495     *
496     * @param name the name of the annotation element; must conform to Java method naming requirements; must not be
497     * {@code null}
498     *
499     * @param defaultValue a {@link SyntheticAnnotationValue} representing the default value; may be {@code null}
500     *
501     * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
502     *
503     * @exception IllegalArgumentException if any argument does not conform to its requirements
504     *
505     * @see #SyntheticAnnotationElement(List, TypeMirror, SyntheticName, SyntheticAnnotationValue)
506     *
507     * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1 Java Language Specification,
508     * section 9.6.1
509     */
510    public SyntheticAnnotationElement(final TypeMirror type, // the "return type"
511                                      final SyntheticName name,
512                                      final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue) {
513      this(List.of(), type, name, defaultValue);
514    }
515
516    /**
517     * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}.
518     *
519     * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
520     * must not be {@code null}
521     *
522     * @param type the type of the annotation element; must conform to Java annotation element type restrictions; must
523     * not be {@code null}
524     *
525     * @param name the name of the annotation element; must conform to Java method naming requirements; must not be
526     * {@code null}
527     *
528     * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
529     *
530     * @exception IllegalArgumentException if any argument does not conform to its requirements
531     *
532     * @see #SyntheticAnnotationElement(List, TypeMirror, SyntheticName, SyntheticAnnotationValue)
533     *
534     * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1 Java Language Specification,
535     * section 9.6.1
536     */
537    public SyntheticAnnotationElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
538                                      final TypeMirror type, // the "return type"
539                                      final SyntheticName name) {
540      this(annotationMirrors, type, name, null);
541    }
542
543    /**
544     * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}.
545     *
546     * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
547     * must not be {@code null}
548     *
549     * @param type the type of the annotation element; must conform to Java annotation element type restrictions; must
550     * not be {@code null}
551     *
552     * @param name the name of the annotation element; must conform to Java method naming requirements; must not be
553     * {@code null}
554     *
555     * @param defaultValue a {@link SyntheticAnnotationValue} representing the default value; may be {@code null}
556     *
557     * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
558     *
559     * @exception IllegalArgumentException if any argument does not conform to its requirements
560     *
561     * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1 Java Language Specification,
562     * section 9.6.1
563     */
564    public SyntheticAnnotationElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
565                                      final TypeMirror type, // the "return type"
566                                      final SyntheticName name,
567                                      final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue) {
568      super();
569      this.annotationMirrors = List.copyOf(annotationMirrors);
570      this.type = switch (type) {
571      case null -> throw new NullPointerException("type");
572      case ArrayType t when t.getKind() == ARRAY -> validateScalarType(t.getComponentType());
573      default -> validateScalarType(type);
574      };
575      if (name.equals("getClass") || name.equals("hashCode") || name.equals("toString")) {
576        // java.lang.Object-declared methods that might otherwise meet annotation element requirements
577        throw new IllegalArgumentException("name: " + name);
578      }
579      this.name = name;
580      this.defaultValue = defaultValue;
581    }
582
583
584    /*
585     * Instance fields.
586     */
587
588
589    final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors() {
590      return this.annotationMirrors;
591    }
592
593    @Override // Object
594    public final boolean equals(final Object other) {
595      return this == other || switch (other) {
596      case null -> false;
597      case SyntheticAnnotationElement sae when this.getClass() == sae.getClass() ->
598      Objects.equals(this.name, sae.name) &&
599      Objects.equals(this.type, sae.type) &&
600      Objects.equals(this.annotationMirrors, sae.annotationMirrors); // TODO: hmm
601      default -> false;
602      };
603    }
604
605    @Override // Object
606    public final int hashCode() {
607      int hashCode = 31;
608      int c = this.name.hashCode();
609      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
610      c = this.type.hashCode();
611      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
612      c = this.annotationMirrors.hashCode(); // TODO: hmm
613      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
614      return hashCode;
615    }
616
617    final SyntheticName name() {
618      return this.name;
619    }
620
621    final TypeMirror type() {
622      return this.type;
623    }
624
625    final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue() {
626      return this.defaultValue;
627    }
628
629  }

699    @Override // DeclaredType (TypeMirror)

701      return this.asElement().toString();
702    }

732                                      final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue) {

839     * Inner and nested classes.
840     */
841
842
843    private static final class Type implements ExecutableType {
844
845
846      /*
847       * Instance fields.
848       */
849
850
851      private final TypeMirror type;
852
853
854      /*
855       * Constructors.
856       */
857
858
859      private Type(final TypeMirror type) { // the "return type"
860        super();
861        this.type = switch (type) {
862        case null -> throw new NullPointerException("type");
863        case ArrayType t when t.getKind() == ARRAY -> validateScalarType(t.getComponentType());
864        default -> validateScalarType(type);
865        };
866      }
867
868
869      /*
870       * Instance methods.
871       */
872
873
874      @Override // TypeMirror
875      public final <R, P> R accept(final TypeVisitor<R, P> v, final P p) {
876        return v.visitExecutable(this, p);
877      }
878
879      @Override // ExecutableType (AnnotatedConstruct)
880      public final <A extends Annotation> A getAnnotation(final Class<A> annotationType) {
881        return null; // deliberate
882      }
883
884      @Override // ExecutableType (AnnotatedConstruct)
885      public final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> getAnnotationMirrors() {
886        return List.of(); // can't actually put type annotations on an executable type to my knowledge
887      }
888
889      @Override // ExecutableType (AnnotatedConstruct)
890      @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
891      public final <A extends Annotation> A[] getAnnotationsByType(final Class<A> annotationType) {
892      return (A[])EMPTY_ANNOTATION_ARRAY; // deliberate
893      }
894
895      @Override // ExecutableType (TypeMirror)
896      public final TypeKind getKind() {
897        return TypeKind.EXECUTABLE;
898      }
899
900      @Override // ExecutableType
901      public final List<? extends TypeMirror> getParameterTypes() {
902        return List.of();
903      }
904
905      @Override // ExecutableType
906      public final NoneType getReceiverType() {
907        return NoneType.of();
908      }
909
910      @Override // ExecutableType
911      public final TypeMirror getReturnType() {
912        return this.type;
913      }
914
915      @Override // ExecutableType
916      public final List<? extends TypeMirror> getThrownTypes() {
917        return List.of();
918      }
919
920      @Override // ExecutableType
921      public final List<? extends TypeVariable> getTypeVariables() {
922        return List.of();
923      }

925    }
